| accessdate = 6 November 2007}}</ref>

;[[Leonid Nevzlin]] : A businessman living in Israel has been accused by [[Russian Procurator's office]] of links to several murders in Russia and was one of the key figures in the [[YUKOS|Yukos oil company]].<ref>{{cite web
     | url = http://www.breitbart.com/news/2006/12/28/061228091432.idx7son5.html
     | title = Russia fingers Israeli fugitive in radiation poison probe
     | accessdate = 11 March 2007 }}</ref>

== Other persons related to the case ==
; [[Yegor Gaidar]] : The sudden illness of [[Yegor Gaidar]] in Ireland on 24 November, the day of Litvinenko's death, has been linked to his visit to the restaurant where polonium was present and is being investigated as part of the overall investigation in the UK and Ireland.<ref>{{cite web
  | last = Anderson
  | first =Paul
  | title = Kildare incident linked to Litvinenko death
  | work = 
  | publisher = [[The Irish Times]]
  | date = 29 November 2006
  | url = http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/breaking/2006/1129/breaking82.htm
  | accessdate = 30 November 2006 }}</ref> However, other observers noted he was probably poisoned after drinking a strange-tasting [[Tea|cup of tea]]. Gaidar was taken to hospital; doctors said his condition is not life-threatening and that he will recover.<ref>{{ru icon}}{{cite web
  | last = 
  | first =
  | title = Gaidar's family and friends refuse to say which hospital he is located in, for fear of his life
