  | accessdate = 2 December 2006 }}</ref> Doctors say that Scaramella was exposed to a much lower level of polonium-210 than Litvinenko had been exposed to, and that preliminary tests found "no evidence of radiation toxicity".<ref>{{cite web
  | last = 
