  | date = 2 December 2006
  | url = http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/16002222/
  | accessdate = 2 December 2006 }}</ref> According to the 6 pm [[channel 4]] (9 December 2006) news the intake of polonium he suffered will only result in a dose of 1 mSv. This will lead to a 1 in 20000 chance of [[cancer]]. According to The Independent, Scaramella alleged that Litvinenko was involved in smuggling radioactive material to Z<U+00FC>rich in 2000.<ref>{{cite web
  | last =Milmo
